laboratory_examinations.findings: Somatotroph, corticotroph, and gonadotroph deficits identified.
Showed partial intrasellar arachnoidocele, hypoplastic anterior pituitary, ectopic posterior pituitary lobe, absent pituitary stalk, and thin anterior corpus callosum.
GH deficiency and TSH deficiency noted.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: ACTH deficiency and hypogonadotroph hypogonadism diagnosed at 23 months and 14 years, respectively.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Showed ectopic posterior pituitary, pituitary stalk interruption, and porencephaly.
Complete GH and TSH deficits, along with symptomatic corticotroph and gonadotroph deficiencies.
